commit.message:
Updates org.freedesktop.impl.portal.Settings backend to v2.

- Added high-contrast setting.
- Added accent-color support.
- Refactored to make it easier to add new settings in the future.

Accent color currently attempts to get an accent color by:
- Matching the name with a static list (currently only Mint themes)
- Failing that, it checks a gsettings key.

commit.message:
Don't exit when we don't support the current desktop, we're expected
to finish registering and provide fallback support.

We declare support for a number of portals in our xapp.portal
definition, but only actually provide a subset of those for Xfce
and MATE.

For other desktops, we can still provide the 'settings' portal,
which isn't dependent on anything else.

Fortunately xdg-desktop-portal handles all of this gracefully.

Fixes #5
